formatted_address: Medini Iskandar Malaysia, 79250 Johor Bahru, Johor, Malaysia
name: Restoran Al Falah JB ( nasi kandar mamu ar)

reviews.text:
Affordable price and big portion.
VIP naan is cheese naan covered in chocolate sauce (abit unusual in my opinion), other than that service is good, waiting time took about 15-20mins for 6 packs of food.

Midnight supper place, the outdoor is cold, i prefer semi covered area feel warmer.

roti canai and naan can improve by make it more crispy.

Maggie goreng is awesome as usual

i bought nasi + kobis + ayam goreng. they charge me RM13. BUT i saw in your cash counter display.  its show RM2.50 Nasi & RM5.50 ayam goreng & RM5 for sayur. are you sure you guys charge RM5 for that little bit kobis ? wahhhhh !!! i know laq its iskandar  puteri medini luxury area. common sense please. most of your customers are workers. please charge reasonable. your customers service is really good but the food quality and price become worst day by day.

I think there may have been a misheard which is we ordered roti puri but the staff heard roti bom. And we told them the order was wrong, then they sent a new one but it took some time and the staff looked irritated.

I had difficulty speaking English with them but the staffs are patience to listen to my order. After repeating several times, there is still 1 order not ordered but can see their effort into in for us. Ordered a beehoon goreng, it was the wok hey taste. Prata is freshly make on the spot. Naan is my disappointment. I ordered a garlic naan, it doesn’t hv garlicky taste at all and it wasn’t bake till crispy.
